💭 Simple echo server listening on port 8888
🏁 ➡️ 🔢 🍇
	🕴🐇💻🔤SCRIPT=$(pwd)/; echo $SCRIPT > currentdir; chmod 600 currentdir🔤 ❗
	😀🔤Created Dir file🔤❗

	🆗dirbytes 📇🐇📄🔤currentdir🔤❗ 🍇
		😀🍺🔡dirbytes❗❗
	🍉
	🙅‍♀️error🍇🍉


	🍺🆕📄▶️📜 🔤currentdir🔤❗️ ➡️ readFile
	😀🔤Dir file opened🔤❗

	🚪readFile❗
	😀🔤Dir file closed🔤❗

	💭Starts listening on 8888
	🍺🆕🏄 8888❗️ ➡️ server
	😀🔤Started listener on 8888🔤❗

	🔁👍🍇
		💭 Opens socket with client
		🍺 🙋 server❗️ ➡️ clientSocket
		🛂🆕🧵 🍇 🎍🥡
			🔁👍🍇
				💭Read 8192 bytes (max size for HTTP requests)
				🆗 data 👂 clientSocket 8192❗️ 🍇
					🍺 💬 clientSocket data❗️
					🔡📏data❓❗ ➡ length
					😀🔤length read: 🧲length🧲❌n❌n🔤❗
					😀🍺🔡 data❗️❗️
					↪🍺🔡🔪data 0 3❗❗ 🙌 🔤GET🔤🍇
						😀🔤GET received🔤❗
						🔍data 📇🔤❌r❌n🔤❗ 0❗ ➡ offset
						😀🔡🍺offset❗❗
						🔪data 0 🍺offset❗ ➡ requestline

						🍺🔡requestline❗ ➡ asciirequestline
						😀🔤Request line: 🧲asciirequestline🧲🔤❗

						🔫asciirequestline 🔤 🔤❗ ➡ requestlist
						🐽requestlist 1❗ ➡ dir
						😀🔤Requested Directory: 🧲dir🧲🔤❗

						🍺🆕📄▶️📜 dir❗️ ➡️ readFile
						😀🔤File opened🔤❗

						🚪readFile❗
						😀🔤File closed🔤❗

					🍉
					↪❎🤜length 🙌 🔤0🔤 🤛❗🍇
						😀🔤End of request data🔤❗
						↩↩
